

	 
      Alecka jumped and grabbed a plate from the cupboard. She loved when her grandma came and visited for a while. Grandma knew so many stories and fun things to do. She grabbed some utensils from the drawer before rushing back to the table to place them beside between Mom and herself. She heard them moving to the kitchen talking and laughing.  Grandmother entered the kitchen with a huge smile with Mom behind her. "Grandma!" Alecka ran to her grandmother and hugged her tightly around the middle.  "Goodness gracious, child. I haven't been gone that long. Now let's sit down and finish supper and you can tell me everything new in your life." Alecka felt Grandma hold her tightly for a moment before pushing her toward her chair at the table.  
     
    
